{
  "stem": "14387.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They said, well, if you want to go, we will help you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I got in touch with my cousin in New York, and he agreed to give us all the papers that we needed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then Norwegian-- we didn't know how to go about that tremendous journey, so the Norwegian government made all the arrangements for us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We would have to-- those days the DC-3 was the largest plane, so they made all the arrangements for us to travel right through to New York.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So we had our tickets and everything arranged, and we had our guarantee.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It took several weeks to get all these things arranged, you can imagine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, when you lived in Europe in those days, America was New York.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You're going to New York.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You didn't go to America.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You went to New York, the Jewish people anyway, so there wasn't any thought that we weren't going to go all the way through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, we had to leave Stockholm in the middle of winter to fly to Moscow, and we were at the airport-- it was a terribly tearful farewell for his mother because she knew she'd never see us again.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was going to be left with her daughter in Stockholm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We knew it would be the last time, so it was a terrible, terrible goodbye.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Went to the airport and they told us the plane could not take off because there were terrible storms in the Balkans, and the plane had to land to get fuel.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because of the storms they would not be able to land.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they didn't have enough fuel to fly directly to Moscow, so we would have to wait till the next day.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
